  "task": "on_demand",
  "output": "Reviewing the AI Marketing Department brand through the lens of the Prism system, here are the top two issues I’ve identified:\n\n1. **Color Token Inconsistency (Product-Brand Gap)**\nThe marketing accent (`#0891B2`) currently used for the department is being applied in an ad-hoc manner within the codebase, rather than being defined as a systematic Prism accent token. This leads to \"AI smell\"—where colors feel chosen for a specific screen rather than part of the unified system—and makes scaling visual consistency across new marketing assets nearly impossible.\n\n2. **Platform Context Mismatch (Variant Drift)**\nThe brand documentation lacks explicit guidance on which Prism variant (Solar/Midnight) applies to the Slack-embedded interface. Given that Slack has a distinct, predominantly light/neutral interface, applying the \"Deep Dark Canvas\" (Midnight) aesthetic directly to the Slack app listing or embedded surfaces without proper variant adaptation risks creating visual noise and diluting our brand's premium, cockpit-like feel.\n\nFixing these requires formalizing the marketing accent as a system-wide design token and defining a specific \"Slack/Platform\" variant of the Prism aesthetic to ensure our presence feels native yet unmistakably Glyphor.\n\n— Mia",
